  "texts": [
    "Deviation ± 0.70 ± 0.85 ± 1.08 ± 0.85 https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0295632.t008",
    "• Sensitivity to the Value of K: The performance of KNN imputation is sensitive to the choice of the number of nearest neighbors (K).",
    "A small K may result in noise being introduced into the imputed values, while a large K may lead to over smoothing and loss of important patterns in the data.",
    "• Curse of Dimensionality: In high-dimensional spaces, the notion of \"nearest neighbors\" becomes less meaningful because all data points tend to be relatively far apart.",
    "This makes KNN less effective in such settings."
  ]
}